---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTABanner from '../../components/CTABanner.astro';

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  'itemListElement': [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 1, 'name': 'Home', 'item': 'https://1404.io/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 2, 'name': 'Case Studies', 'item': 'https://1404.io/case-studies/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 3, 'name': 'The Construct Group' },
  ],
};
---

<PageLayout
  title="The Construct Group — Case Study — 1404"
  description="From spreadsheets to a unified operations platform. 12 integrated modules, AI agent teams, and ongoing technology leadership. Built and deployed in two months."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-20">
      <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-text-muted mb-4">Case Study</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-text-primary leading-tight">
        The Construct Group
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg mt-6 leading-relaxed">
        From spreadsheets to a unified platform. In two months.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- The Challenge -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">The Challenge</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The Construct Group is a retail fixture installation company. National footprint. 50+ workers in the field at any given time. Projects spanning every major retail chain you've walked into.
        </p>
        <p>
          When we met them, they were stuck at levels 2 through 4 on the progression. Spreadsheets for labor forecasting. Manual purchase order processing. Inventory tracked by memory and phone calls. Scheduling that lived in someone's head. A dozen disconnected tools that didn't talk to each other.
        </p>
        <p>
          The operations worked. They'd been working for years. But the manual overhead was enormous. Every project manager spent hours on administrative tasks that should have taken minutes. Information moved through the company at the speed of email. Decisions were made with incomplete data because pulling complete data took too long.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What We Built -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">What We Built</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-10">
        <p>
          A unified operations platform. 182,442 lines of production code. 93 database tables. 12 integrated modules. Over 100 pages of interface. Built in approximately two months by one person.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-border pl-8">
        <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-text-muted mb-6">The Modules</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-y-3 gap-x-8 text-text-secondary text-sm">
          <p>Project Management</p>
          <p>Labor Forecasting</p>
          <p>Purchase Orders</p>
          <p>Inventory Management</p>
          <p>Scheduling & Dispatch</p>
          <p>Financial Tracking</p>
          <p>Vendor Management</p>
          <p>Reporting & Analytics</p>
          <p>Worker Management</p>
          <p>Client Portal</p>
          <p>Document Management</p>
          <p>AI Operations Agent</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Results -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-8">What Changed</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Before the platform, TCG's project managers spent a significant part of their day on administrative work — manually compiling labor forecasts, processing purchase orders by hand, tracking inventory through phone calls and spreadsheets, and assembling reports from disconnected systems. Information moved through the company at the speed of email, and decisions were made with whatever data someone could pull together in the moment.
        </p>
        <p>
          After deployment, those workflows moved into a single integrated system. Labor forecasting that used to require manual data compilation runs automatically. Purchase orders that involved multiple steps of manual entry and approval routing now flow through the system in minutes. Inventory is tracked in real time instead of reconciled after the fact. Financial data, project status, and operational metrics are all available in one place without anyone having to assemble them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The AI agent team handles daily executive operations — morning intelligence briefs, email triage, meeting preparation, and operational monitoring. TCG's leadership gets a synthesized view of the business every morning before their day starts, built from actual system data rather than someone's summary.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result was significant enough that TCG came on as an equity partner. Ben Barnes, TCG's CEO, now actively refers other operators to 1404.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Compounding Effect -->
    <div class="border-t border-border pt-16">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-8">The Compounding Effect</h2>

      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper-dim pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Month 1</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            Core platform live. Team onboarding. Immediate wins in PO processing and labor forecasting. The system is learning the company's patterns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper-dim pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Month 12</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            AI agents know every workflow. Automated monitoring catches problems before they surface. The system has observed thousands of decisions and understands the business at a level no single employee does.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Month 24</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            Institutional knowledge is embedded in the technology. The system doesn't just support operations. It drives them. The competitive advantage is permanent. A new competitor starting from zero cannot close this gap.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABanner />
</PageLayout>
